info.title: Washington State Department of Education API
info.description: Endpoints for student demographics by district in Washington State

get.description: This endpoint returns all school districts and includes its name, slug(used for querying about an individual district) and number, as well as the name and basic enrollment data

parameters.name: per_page
parameters.description: the number of objects you would like returned on each page. Defaults to 25 if not provided

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: which page of the response you would like returned. Defaults to 1 if not provided

schema.description: contains error message and status code

get.description: This endpoint returns all counties and includes its name, slug(used for querying about an individual district) and number, as well as the name, number, and slug of all all districts within that county

parameters.name: per_page
parameters.description: the number of objects you would like returned on each page. Defaults to 25 if not provided

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: which page of the response you would like returned. Defaults to 1 if not provided

schema.description: contains error message and status code

get.summary: Student demographics for specified district in given year
get.description: This endpoint returns the gender, race & ethnicity, students who receive exceptional student services, and other demographic information on all students in the specified county for the specified school year. County name should be passed as the parameterized version (slug). The school year should be passed as the full year for the starting year, and the last two digits of the ending year. This can only span one school year. For example - '2016-17'. The state has provided slightly different data for each school year, so there may be some empty values. NOTE: if the number in foster care is -10, that means that the district provided a result of 'N<10'

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: school year for which data is being requested

schema.description: contains error message and status code

404.description: Data does not exist for the specified combination of school district and school year. Includes specifics for which parameter could not be found

schema.description: contains error message and status code

get.summary: Student demographics for specified district in given year
get.description: This endpoint returns the gender, race & ethnicity, students who receive exceptional student services, and other demographic information on all students in Washington State. The school year should be passed as the full year for the starting year, and the last two digits of the ending year. This can only span one school year. For example - '2016-17'. The state has provided slightly different data for each school year, so there may be some empty values. NOTE: if the number in foster care is -10, that means that the district provided a result of 'N<10'

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: school year for which data is being requested

schema.description: contains error message and status code

404.description: Data does not exist for the school year. Includes specifics for which parameter could not be found

schema.description: contains error message and status code

get.summary: Five year graduation rates for the specified school district and year
get.description: This endpoint returns the gender, race & ethnicity, students who receive exceptional student services, and other demographic information on all students in the specified school district for the specified school year. School district name should be passed as the parameterized version (slug). The school year should be passed as the full year for the starting year, and the last two digits of the ending year. This can only span one school year. For example - '2016-17' (This year would produce results for the class of 2016)

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: school year for which data is being requested

parameters.name: graduation_tag
parameters.description: name of tag you would like response to be scoped by. Options are - 'all', 'race ethnicity', 'other', 'gender', 'exceptional student services'. Limit 1.

schema.description: contains error message and status code

404.description: Data does not exist for the specified combination of school district and school year. Includes specifics for which parameter could not be found

schema.description: contains error message and status code

get.summary: Five year graduation rates for the specified county and year
get.description: This endpoint returns the gender, race & ethnicity, students who receive exceptional student services, and other demographic information on all students in the specified school district for the specified school year. School district name should be passed as the parameterized version (slug). The school year should be passed as the full year for the starting year, and the last two digits of the ending year. This can only span one school year. For example - '2016-17' (This year would produce results for the class of 2016)

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: school year for which data is being requested

parameters.name: graduation_tag
parameters.description: name of tag you would like response to be scoped by. Options are - 'all', 'race ethnicity', 'other', 'gender', 'exceptional student services'. Limit 1.

schema.description: contains error message and status code

404.description: Data does not exist for the specified combination of county and school year. Includes specifics for which parameter could not be found
